articles.description: Members of the Michigan State faculty voted 61-4 to express no confidence in the eight-member governing body at the university. Meanwhile, the institution's interim president wrote to the campus community about cooperation with ongoing investigations.
articles.headline: Michigan State faculty delivers no-confidence vote on board of trustees

images.caption: The Michigan State faculty's vote against the board of trustees came largely in response to the board's decision to name John Engler the school's interim president.

images.caption: Michigan State students, including one who jumped onto and sat on the middle of a table, interrupt an MSU board of trustees meeting to protest the school's selection of John Engler as the interim president.
images.name: MSU students vent frustration over interim president selection

videos.description: Theo Pinson goes up for a rebound but lands awkwardly on the court and needs assistance to the bench. Pinson would head to the locker room.
videos.headline: Pinson heads to UNC locker room after awkward fall

videos.description: Gabe DeVoe hits his third triple of the first half on a sweet step-back move to extend the Tigers' lead over the Tar Heels.
videos.headline: Clemson's DeVoe on fire from 3

videos.description: Clemson's Aamir Simms grabs the rebound and starts the break as Elijah Thomas gets the ball in transition and finishes with a dunk.
videos.headline: Clemson pushes the pace with transition dunk

videos.description: As the clock winds down, Clyde Trapp launches a 3-pointer that finds nothing but net for Clemson's tenth triple of the half.
videos.headline: Trapp drains Clemson's 10th triple at buzzer

videos.description: Kenny Williams gets the pass and spots up from well beyond the arc to hit the triple and the foul.
videos.headline: Williams sparks UNC with 4-point play

videos.description: The Tar Heels gain control of the loose ball and Cameron Johnson drains the 3-pointer to cut the deficit to 52-48.
videos.headline: UNC roaring back with hectic 3

videos.description: Clemson extends its 2nd half lead on North Carolina after Elijah Thomas gets the ball in the post and goes up strong for the and-1 bucket.
videos.headline: Clemson controls lead on Thomas and-1

videos.description: Cameron Johnson is shooting lights out from beyond the arc, making 6 of his 10 attempts as North Carolina trails Clemson 70-67.
videos.headline: Johnson hits 6th triple

videos.description: Tied 74-74, the Tigers swing the ball around to Marcquise Reed who drains the open triple giving Clemson the lead back. Clemson goes on to beat North Carolina 82-78.
videos.headline: Clemson regains lead on Reed's triple

videos.description: Clemson fends off North Carolina and wins 82-78 while Tiger fans celebrate with the players on the court.
videos.headline: Victorious Clemson fans storm court
